1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:00,900
hello everyone

2
00:00:00,900 --> 00:00:02,966
and if you have been following my latest run

3
00:00:02,966 --> 00:00:04,600
you know I haven't been passive anything

4
00:00:04,600 --> 00:00:06,400
but I have been doing everything on demand

5
00:00:07,133 --> 00:00:08,900
that caused a little bit of discussions

6
00:00:08,966 --> 00:00:12,533
so I'm going to make this video to better explain why of this decision

7
00:00:12,933 --> 00:00:19,500
and while the main reason was actually that I simply wanted to play in a different way than the usual Factorio Satisfactory way of making passive lines

8
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:22,733
I figured out this way is actually a little bit better

9
00:00:23,133 --> 00:00:25,666
and right here I think we can see the main difference

10
00:00:26,166 --> 00:00:27,566
I am currently in UHV

11
00:00:27,566 --> 00:00:30,800
and my world base has a single Mega Distillation Tower

12
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:33,700
and especially in single player that means that

13
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:36,300
I won't have to upgrade a distillation tower for the platline

14
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:39,266
I won't have to upgrade a distillation tower for the naquadah-line

15
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:42,466
I won't have to upgrade a distillation tower for the netherite-line

16
00:00:42,566 --> 00:00:45,333
I have a single Mega Distillation Tower to worry about

17
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:47,966
I think that could already sum up the whole video

18
00:00:47,966 --> 00:00:52,000
but let's better see what it means to have a single machine for each kind of task

19
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:54,100
and also how to manage it

20
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:57,400
and at this point I realize that maybe I shouldn't even be finishing this video

21
00:00:57,566 --> 00:01:01,700
one of the main reason for saying that is that I'm lazy and also I'm not good at explaining things

22
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,966
the main reason is that there isn't really anything to explain

23
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:06,900
it's just that for me now

24
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:10,466
it's more fun to build a single machine and figure out how to make patterns that work

25
00:01:10,766 --> 00:01:14,066
rather than spamming machines where stuff goes in and stuff comes out

26
00:01:14,366 --> 00:01:16,333
and while I was playing in this weird way

27
00:01:16,333 --> 00:01:19,500
I realized it took me only half an hour to set up kevlar

28
00:01:19,666 --> 00:01:24,800
which is way faster than when it took me one whole weekend to make a passive line dedicated to kevlar

29
00:01:25,166 --> 00:01:27,933
and since I drastically reduced the amount of machines I have

30
00:01:27,933 --> 00:01:29,466
it takes less time to upgrade those

31
00:01:29,466 --> 00:01:31,100
and they also produce less lag

32
00:01:31,533 --> 00:01:33,533
some people may argue that if I play that way

33
00:01:33,533 --> 00:01:34,966
I will have more level maintainers

34
00:01:34,966 --> 00:01:36,566
and those will be a source of lag

35
00:01:36,566 --> 00:01:39,333
but I think that's only if you set those improperly

36
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,933
and I think that's it about this video

37
00:01:41,933 --> 00:01:44,300
which was only about this different way of playing

38
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:51,800
a better explanation on how to do it I think belongs more to a AE2 or a GregTech tutorial video rather than this one

39
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:53,433
so see you next time

40
00:01:53,433 --> 00:01:53,900
bye bye

41
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:00,900
大家好

42
00:00:00,900 --> 00:00:02,966
如果你有关注我最近的游戏直播（TST）

43
00:00:02,966 --> 00:00:04,600
你应该知道我没有把所有东西都变成被动生产

44
00:00:04,600 --> 00:00:06,400
而是按需/下单做所有东西

45
00:00:07,133 --> 00:00:08,900
这也引发了一些讨论

46
00:00:08,966 --> 00:00:12,533
所以我做这个视频，是想更清楚地说明我作这个决定的原因

47
00:00:12,933 --> 00:00:19,500
主要原因其实很简单：我只是想用不同于通常（像 Factorio 或 Satisfactory）的做法来玩，不再一味做被动产线

48
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:22,733
我发现我的做法其实更有优势一些

49
00:00:23,133 --> 00:00:25,666
在这里，我想我们可以看出主要的不同之处

50
00:00:26,166 --> 00:00:27,566
我现在在 UHV 阶段

51
00:00:27,566 --> 00:00:30,800
我的基地里只有一座大型蒸馏塔

52
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:33,700
尤其是在单人游戏，这意味着

53
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:36,300
我不用为铂处理去升级蒸馏塔

54
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:39,266
不用为硅岩产线升级蒸馏塔

55
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:42,466
不用为下界合金产线升级蒸馏塔

56
00:00:42,566 --> 00:00:45,333
我只需要操心这一座大型蒸馏塔

57
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:47,966
这差不多就是整个视频要表达的意思

58
00:00:47,966 --> 00:00:52,000
但我们还是来看看，每项任务只用一台机器到底意味着什么

59
00:00:52,333 --> 00:00:54,100
以及如何去管理它们

60
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:57,400
我现在想到，也许根本没必要把这个视频做得太长

61
00:00:57,566 --> 00:01:01,700
其中一个主要原因是我比较懒，而且不太擅长解释事情

62
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,966
真正的原因是，其实也没什么好解释的

63
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:06,900
只是现在对我来说

64
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:10,466
建造一台机器并弄清楚如何设计出可行的样板更有意思

65
00:01:10,766 --> 00:01:14,066
而不是堆很多机器，让东西进进出出

66
00:01:14,366 --> 00:01:16,333
当我用这种“奇怪的”方式玩的时候

67
00:01:16,333 --> 00:01:19,500
我发现只花了半个小时就能把凯夫拉产线搭好

68
00:01:19,666 --> 00:01:24,800
这比我以前花一整个周末去搭一条专门的凯夫拉被动产线要快得多

69
00:01:25,166 --> 00:01:27,933
而且因为大幅减少了机器数量的缘故

70
00:01:27,933 --> 00:01:29,466
升级它们所需的时间也更少

71
00:01:29,466 --> 00:01:31,100
同时也能减少卡顿

72
00:01:31,533 --> 00:01:33,533
有人可能会说，如果我这么玩

73
00:01:33,533 --> 00:01:34,966
我会需要更多的 ME 请求器

74
00:01:34,966 --> 00:01:36,566
这些可能会成为卡顿的来源

75
00:01:36,566 --> 00:01:39,333
不过我认为，这只有在你设置不当的情况下才会发生

76
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,933
这差不多就是本视频的全部内容

77
00:01:41,933 --> 00:01:44,300
这只是对这种不同玩法的介绍

78
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:51,800
关于如何具体实现，我觉得更适合放在 AE2 或 GT 的教程视频里，而不是在这段视频里

79
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:53,433
下次见

80
00:01:53,433 --> 00:01:53,900
拜拜

